# Digital Clock Web Application

## Description

Digital Clock Web Application is a lightweight front-end project developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

The application displays the current system time in a clean digital clock interface and updates automatically in real time. It demonstrates fundamental web development concepts such as DOM manipulation, time-based functions, and dynamic content rendering.

This project was created as a practical exercise to strengthen JavaScript programming skills and understand real-time user interface updates.

## Technologies

The project was developed using the following technologies:

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript (Vanilla JavaScript)

## Features

### Real-Time Time Display

* Displays the current system time
* Automatically updates every second
* No page refresh required

### Dynamic User Interface

* Live DOM updates
* Responsive clock rendering
* Minimal and clean design

### Automatic Time Formatting

* Leading zero formatting
* Consistent digital clock appearance
* Easy-to-read display format

### Lightweight Architecture

* No external libraries
* No frameworks required
* Pure client-side implementation

## Technologies Demonstrated

This project showcases practical implementation of:

* JavaScript Date Object
* DOM Manipulation
* Event Scheduling
* Real-Time UI Updates
* HTML Structure
* CSS Styling
* Front-End Development Fundamentals

