## Installation

### Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/digital-clock-web-app.git

cd digital-clock-web-app
```

### Run the Application

No installation process is required.

Simply open the `index.html` file in any modern web browser.

Alternatively, launch a local development server:

```bash
python -m http.server 8000
```

Then navigate to:

```text
http://localhost:8000
```

## Usage

### Step 1: Open the Application

Launch the project in a web browser.

### Step 2: View Current Time

The application automatically displays the current system time.

### Step 3: Real-Time Updates

The displayed time updates continuously without requiring user interaction.

## Application Workflow

The system performs the following operations:

1. Retrieves the current system time using JavaScript.
2. Extracts hour and minute values.
3. Formats values using leading zeros when necessary.
4. Updates the displayed content within the DOM.
5. Refreshes the displayed time every second using a timer function.

## Example Output

```text
14 : 08
```

## Learning Objectives

This project demonstrates:

* JavaScript Functions
* Working with Date Objects
* DOM Element Selection
* Dynamic Content Rendering
* Real-Time User Interface Updates
* Event Scheduling with setInterval()
* Front-End Application Development

## Limitations

* Displays local system time only.
* No timezone selection support.
* No date display functionality.
* No alarm or timer features.
* No synchronization with external time services.

